result.execSummary:
The defendant Zakirah Etoya Burris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: The same conditions imposed for probation shall apply to extended supervision.

miscConds.notes: lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling, assessments, and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent. 

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. 

Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Jail for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substance. 

Defendant shall have no contact with Nathanial B. or Zyiah S.

Defendant shall not operate any motor vehicle without a valid drivers license. 

Defendant shall not be a passenger in any motor vehicle unless the driver is the valid/legal owner of the vehicle.

timeConds.notes: Defendant shall complete 40 hours of documented community service
